    "Specifically, we delve into a comparative analysis of the performance of encoder-only models against the latest and more substantial decoder-only architectures, in the context of intent classification and sentiment analysis.",
    "We scrutinize their effectiveness, computational demands, and practical implications, with a particular emphasis on the question of whether the colossal scale of newer decode-only LLMs is indispensable for real-world applications, or if smaller, yet proficient, models like BERT can provide pragmatic and resource-efficient solutions.",
    "Motivating this inquiry is the growing concern about the computational demands, energy consumption, and deployment challenges associated with large-scale models.Through this exploration, we aim to provide valuable insights that guide researchers and practitioners in selecting models that align with the specific requirements of their applications.The main contributions of this work are as follows:• A comprehensive comparison of the performance of an encoder-only model and a larger decoder-only on intent classification and sentiment analysis.",
    "• An analysis of the factors contributing to the observed performance differences.",
    "• Insights into the computational demands of each model family.The remainder of this paper is organized as follows."
